Title: An Act to Identify United States Citizenship Status on Driver's
Official Title: An Act to Identify United States Citizenship Status on Driver's
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1329
H.P. 864 House of Representatives, March 27, 2025
Licenses and Nondriver Identification Cards
Reference to the Committee on Transportation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative GREENWOOD of Wales.
Cosponsored by Senator BICKFORD of Androscoggin and
Representatives: CARUSO of Caratunk, COLLINS of Sidney, HAGGAN of Hampden,
QUINT of Hodgdon, SMITH of Palermo, WHITE of Guilford, Senators: BERNARD of
Aroostook, CYRWAY of Kennebec.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 29-A MRSA §1401, sub-§1, as amended by PL 1995, c. 482, Pt. A, §24, is
3 further amended to read:
4 1. Required information. A license must state, at a minimum, the name, date of birth,
5 place of residence or mailing address if different from the residence, of the licensee and the
6 permanent number assigned to that licensee. A license also must state whether the licensee
7 is a citizen of the United States, a noncitizen of the United States or an asylum seeker. A
8 name displayed on a license must be as the name appears on a birth certificate or a court
9 order or as the result of marriage.
10 Sec. 2. 29-A MRSA §1410, sub-§2, ¶C, as amended by PL 2001, c. 671, §27, is
11 further amended to read:
12 C. The applicant's date of birth; and
13 Sec. 3. 29-A MRSA §1410, sub-§2, ¶E, as enacted by PL 1997, c. 437, §40, is
14 amended to read:
15 E. Any other information and identification that the Secretary of State by rule requires.;
16 and
17 Sec. 4. 29-A MRSA §1410, sub-§2, ¶F is enacted to read:
18 F. A designation as to whether the applicant is a citizen of the United States, a
19 noncitizen of the United States or an asylum seeker.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This bill requires a driver's license and a nondriver identification card to state whether
2222 the licensee or card holder is a citizen of the United States, a noncitizen of the United States
2233 or an asylum seeker.
